{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"alias":"fine-facet-web","description":"# S4a — Review-bot Gerrit identity + event plumbing (plugins, SSM token, IAM)\n\n## Why\nBefore the review-bot can vote (S4b), the Gerrit-side plumbing must exist: a service-account\nidentity the bot votes as, the event-delivery plugins that notify it, and the secrets/IAM to\nreach them. Split out from the bot's review/vote LOGIC (S4b) because this is a distinct layer\n(Gerrit account + plugin install + AWS IAM/SSM) with no application logic — keeping each story\nsingle-layered (the S4 oversize the gate flagged was 4 layers in one ticket).\n\n## What\n- **Bot identity.** A dedicated Gerrit account in the built-in `Service Users` group (thread\n  isolation; SERVICE_USER accounts are excluded from the attention set except on a negative\n  vote). Its HTTP auth token (for the OUTBOUND REST vote in S4b) is stored in SSM Parameter\n  Store at a fixed path (e.g. `/rebar/gerrit/bot-token`). `infra/gerrit/service-user.sh` is\n  **idempotent**: check-before-create (`GET /a/accounts/<bot>`) and `put-parameter --overwrite`,\n  so re-provisioning never duplicates the account or orphans a token.\n- **Least-privilege IAM.** The instance role grants `ssm:GetParameter` scoped to exactly the bot\n  parameter path (`arn:aws:ssm:<region>:<acct>:parameter/rebar/gerrit/*`), never `Resource:\"*\"`.\n- **Event delivery — two integrated channels.**\n  - *Push (primary):* install the `webhooks` plugin to POST `patchset-created` to the review-bot\n    receiver (the HTTP endpoint stood up in S2, behavior wired in S4b).\n  - *Backfill (safety net):* install the `events-log` plugin, which STORES a queryable event log\n    (`GET /a/plugins/events-log/events?...`) — it does NOT auto-replay; the S4b reconciler polls\n    it. Plugin **provenance is a durable end-state, not a research note**: the exact arm64 jar\n    URLs + checksums + versions for Gerrit 3.14.1 are pinned in `infra/gerrit/` (recorded files),\n    so a rebuild installs byte-identical plugins.\n- **Inbound webhook auth (peer-pattern correction — the `webhooks` plugin has NO HMAC).** The\n  Gerrit `webhooks` plugin offers no request signing/HMAC (only `sslVerify`, which defaults\n  false). So inbound authenticity is bolt-on and split across the boundary: S4a configures the\n  webhook with a **secret token in the URL** (`remote.<name>.url =\n  https://rebar.solutions.navateam.com/review/?token=<secret-from-SSM>`) and restricts exposure\n  via **network ACL / nginx** so the `/review/` path is only reachable from the Gerrit host\n  (loopback/SG). S4b's receiver validates the token + source. (Documented as the inbound-auth\n  contract; the secret lives in SSM, not in `refs/meta/config` in plaintext where avoidable.)\n\n## Scope\nIn: the Gerrit Service-Users bot account + SSM token + least-privilege IAM + install/pin the\n`webhooks` and `events-log` plugins + the inbound webhook secret/ACL config. Out: the receiver's\nparse/review/vote/reconcile LOGIC and observability (S4b); replication (S5). Depends on S3\n(project + `LLM-Review` label/ACL exist so the bot's vote permission resolves) and S2 (the\nreceiver service + nginx `/review/` route exist).\n\n## Files\n- `infra/gerrit/service-user.sh` — idempotent bot-account creation + SSM token upsert.\n- `infra/gerrit/webhooks.config` — `webhooks` plugin remote config (patchset-created -> the\n  `/review/` receiver, with the secret-token URL) + `allowedUrlPattern` if used.\n- `infra/gerrit/plugins/` — pinned `webhooks` + `events-log` jar provenance (URLs + checksums +\n  versions for 3.14.1/arm64) and the install step.\n- the least-privilege SSM IAM policy for the bot token path (in the infra Terraform).\n\n> Record `set_file_impact` for these paths before claiming.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] The bot account exists in `Service Users` (SERVICE_USER tag; excluded from the attention\n      set except on a negative vote); its REST auth token is sourced from SSM; re-running\n      `service-user.sh` is idempotent (no duplicate account / orphaned token).\n- [ ] The instance role's SSM read is scoped to the bot token path only (no `Resource:\"*\"`),\n      verified against the attached policy.\n- [ ] The `webhooks` and `events-log` plugins are installed on Gerrit 3.14.1 from pinned,\n      checksum-verified, arm64-compatible jars whose URLs/checksums/versions are recorded in\n      `infra/gerrit/` (a rebuild reinstalls byte-identical plugins).\n- [ ] The `webhooks` remote is configured to POST `patchset-created` to the `/review/` receiver\n      using a secret-token URL (secret from SSM), and the `/review/` path is reachable only from\n      the Gerrit host (network ACL / nginx), since the plugin provides no HMAC — verified by a\n      request without the token/from a disallowed source being refused at the edge.\n- [ ] `events-log` is installed and queryable (the S4b reconciler depends on it); confirmed by a\n      sample `GET /a/plugins/events-log/events` returning recent events.","id":"42ba-ca47-e824-49b9","parent_id":"d251-05e1-eb55-43b2","priority":2,"tags":["gerrit","mcp"],"ticket_type":"story","title":"infra: S4a — Review-bot Gerrit identity + event plumbing (plugins, SSM token, IAM)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1782699639253424001,"uuid":"2eb5a7c5-8eb8-4c5f-8c50-8e7ec3027e5c"}